17:57.577 --> 17:59.779
- I believe in you,
Crystal Joe.

17:59.912 --> 18:01.114
You're gonna get out of here.

18:01.248 --> 18:04.251
I never did. But you will.

18:04.384 --> 18:06.386
Promise me.

18:06.519 --> 18:08.788
- I promise.

18:08.921 --> 18:11.491
- What are you two
whispering about?

18:11.624 --> 18:13.493
- Crystal Joe promised me
she's gonna get herself

18:13.626 --> 18:15.962
on TV someday.
- That right?

18:16.095 --> 18:18.265
Yeah, you got
a good voice for it.

18:18.398 --> 18:19.632
- You think?
- Mm-hmm.

18:19.766 --> 18:21.934
Of course, the, uh,

18:22.068 --> 18:24.737
crooked horse teeth are a problem.

18:24.871 --> 18:26.973
And you got a few extra pounds.

18:27.106 --> 18:30.109
- Landon, what a thing to say.

18:32.545 --> 18:35.047
I'll tell you what, kiddo.

18:35.182 --> 18:37.950
I'll pay to get
your teeth fixed.

18:38.084 --> 18:39.686
- You will?
- Mm-hmm.

18:39.819 --> 18:43.456
You and me will make
it happen together. Deal?

18:43.590 --> 18:45.292
- No. Say no.

18:48.027 --> 18:49.662
- Deal.
- All right.

18:52.432 --> 18:54.334
- Christine.

18:54.467 --> 18:57.370
- Why did you bring me here?

18:57.504 --> 19:00.973
- It's a taste of the
Madeleine soaked in tea.

19:01.107 --> 19:05.245
Proust. A taste from youth can
unlock a lifetime of memories,

19:05.378 --> 19:06.913
and not always good ones.

19:07.046 --> 19:10.517
- I let go of that girl
and that life decades ago.

19:10.650 --> 19:11.818
As far as I'm concerned,

19:11.951 --> 19:14.020
Crystal Joe Stevens
never existed.

19:14.153 --> 19:15.555
- Crystal Joe Stevens had a mom

19:15.688 --> 19:19.359
who loved her so much
and believed in her.

19:19.492 --> 19:21.594
- I came to Fantasy Island
to stuff my face,

19:21.728 --> 19:23.430
and I'm really, really hungry,

19:23.563 --> 19:26.566
so can you please just get me
back to the damn buffet?!

19:26.699 --> 19:29.068
- Yes. Of course.

19:53.260 --> 20:00.166
<i>* *</i>

20:07.340 --> 20:11.344
- 8.5. Can I...join you?

20:11.478 --> 20:14.347
- Sure, but gotta warn you,

20:14.481 --> 20:16.115
I'm feeling good.

20:16.249 --> 20:17.417
- Okay.

20:19.252 --> 20:26.158
<i>* *</i>

20:40.139 --> 20:41.841
I'm Ruby.

20:41.974 --> 20:43.276
<i>- Yo soy Isla.</i>

20:43.410 --> 20:45.778
- Okay.

20:54.421 --> 20:57.390
- I think maybe
I'm lucky I met you.

20:58.358 --> 21:02.762
- Oh, uh, I should...
I should go.

21:02.895 --> 21:05.565
Yeah.
But it was...

21:05.698 --> 21:07.467
nice to meet you.

21:23.049 --> 21:24.250
- Mmm, mmm, mmm.

21:24.384 --> 21:25.618
- Crystal Joe.

21:29.889 --> 21:31.658
- Landon?

21:37.263 --> 21:39.131
- I missed you, kiddo.

21:43.803 --> 21:46.839
- How did he get here?
- Good question.

21:46.973 --> 21:49.041
Now a better question is
why is he here?

21:49.175 --> 21:52.512
- Uh, to mess with me,
to ruin my life.

21:55.548 --> 21:58.150
Do you know when you get a song
stuck in your head,

21:58.284 --> 21:59.686
a song you can't stand

21:59.819 --> 22:02.989
but it's just stuck
in your head for weeks?

22:03.122 --> 22:07.527
Landon was in my head
for years.

22:07.660 --> 22:10.296
When my mom died,
I was stuck with him.

22:10.430 --> 22:13.332
But I got away.

22:13.466 --> 22:15.468
I remade my whole life.

22:15.602 --> 22:17.404
- Did you get away,
Crystal Joe?

22:17.537 --> 22:19.138
- Don't call me that.
- Or did you just start

22:19.271 --> 22:20.873
listening to the meanness
in other voices?

22:21.007 --> 22:22.875
Because yes, yes, you left.

22:23.009 --> 22:26.178
But did you escape?
Hmm?

22:26.312 --> 22:28.981
No, no. Mm-mm.

22:29.115 --> 22:32.385
That is manchineel fruit.
It's poison fruit.

22:32.519 --> 22:35.688
- You keep poison fruit
on your desk?

22:35.822 --> 22:38.324
- It's a good reminder,
I think,

22:38.458 --> 22:40.192
that things are not
always as they seem.

22:40.326 --> 22:41.828
You certainly aren't.

22:43.095 --> 22:44.697
You know what,

22:44.831 --> 22:46.633
I'm gonna have the servers
bring a meal to your room.

22:46.766 --> 22:48.000
Do you have
any special requests?

22:48.134 --> 22:51.504
- Yes. No. Oh, God.

22:51.638 --> 22:53.039
I've been craving something,

22:53.172 --> 22:55.374
but I just--I cannot
put my finger on what.

22:57.510 --> 22:59.479
- Okay, I'll have the kitchen
send a selection.

23:05.084 --> 23:08.455
<i>* *</i>

23:08.588 --> 23:11.257
- Check it out.
Let's go do some drugs.

23:13.125 --> 23:15.495
Mel Akuda, we've never
done drugs in our life.

23:15.628 --> 23:18.364
And this isn't drugs.
It's goo.

23:18.498 --> 23:21.568
- It's Island Magic.
It opens up new ways of seeing.

23:21.701 --> 23:23.235
It's quite safe. I assure you.

23:23.369 --> 23:26.272
- Well, Ms. Roarke,
we are having the best time.

23:26.405 --> 23:28.941
- Oh, I'm so glad to hear it.
And it's Elena, by the way.

23:29.075 --> 23:32.712
- Aw.
- Enjoy the Island Magic.

23:32.845 --> 23:34.947
The night is young.
-

23:37.917 --> 23:41.153
- Mmm?
- You are a terrible influence.

23:41.287 --> 23:44.290
- Well, we won't tell the kids.
- Mmm.

23:52.131 --> 23:55.401
- You're late, Captain.
- I know. I know.

23:55.535 --> 23:57.737
Late for a very important date.

23:57.870 --> 24:01.808
To talk about the departure
schedule. Sorry.

24:01.941 --> 24:05.444
- I broke out the good stuff.
- I see that.

24:05.578 --> 24:07.446
Want to talk about it?

24:08.648 --> 24:10.750
- No.

24:14.220 --> 24:16.656
- Okay.

24:16.789 --> 24:21.093
It's one of the guests,
Ruby Akuda.

24:21.227 --> 24:25.698
You know, I--I can usually
maintain an emotional distance

24:25.832 --> 24:27.667
from the guests.

24:27.800 --> 24:29.969
If I didn't,
I'd get lost in their needs,

24:30.102 --> 24:31.638
and then I wouldn't be able
to do my job.

24:33.906 --> 24:36.743
But with this lady,
with Ruby...

24:36.876 --> 24:38.811
mm...

24:38.945 --> 24:40.613
it's different.

24:43.415 --> 24:45.284
- 'Cause she's dying.

24:46.586 --> 24:48.354
- I'm sad for her.

24:50.222 --> 24:52.959
And I'm sad for me too, and...

24:53.092 --> 24:55.027
doesn't usually happen.

24:59.932 --> 25:01.601
- You know what I think?

25:01.734 --> 25:04.604
I think Mrs. Ruby Akuda
found a ladder

25:04.737 --> 25:07.774
and climbed over
that wall around your heart.

25:07.907 --> 25:10.009
- It's not a wall. Mm-mm.

25:10.142 --> 25:11.343
It's a moat.

25:14.681 --> 25:16.182
- Anything I can do to help?

25:16.315 --> 25:19.218
- You can pour me another.

25:19.351 --> 25:22.454
- I can do that.

25:33.499 --> 25:39.939
<i>* *</i>

25:40.072 --> 25:43.075
<i>- * You *</i>

25:43.209 --> 25:46.112
<i>* I'd be lost without you *</i>

25:46.245 --> 25:49.882
<i>* *</i>

25:50.016 --> 25:53.252
<i>* You *</i>

25:53.385 --> 25:54.854
<i>* I'd be lost without you *</i>

25:54.987 --> 25:58.758
- I can see your breath.
You smell like perfume.

25:58.891 --> 26:01.293
<i>- * I'd be lost without you *</i>

26:01.427 --> 26:03.229
<i>* *</i>

26:03.362 --> 26:05.564
<i>* I'd be lost without you *</i>

26:05.698 --> 26:10.002
<i>* Ooh ooh *</i>

26:10.136 --> 26:12.805
<i>* You *</i>

26:12.939 --> 26:18.144
<i>* I'd be lost without you *</i>

26:18.277 --> 26:21.080
<i>* I'd be lost
without you *</i>

26:21.213 --> 26:23.549
<i>* *</i>

26:23.683 --> 26:28.487
<i>* I'd be lost without you
ooh ooh *</i>

26:28.621 --> 26:29.989
<i>* *</i>

26:30.122 --> 26:33.125
<i>* You *</i>

26:33.259 --> 26:35.928
<i>* I'd be lost without you *</i>

26:36.062 --> 26:39.866
<i>* Ooh ooh *</i>

26:39.999 --> 26:43.002
<i>* You *</i>

26:43.135 --> 26:46.105
<i>* I'd be lost without you *</i>

26:46.238 --> 26:49.141
<i>* Ooh ooh *</i>

26:49.275 --> 26:50.710
<i>* Oh you... *</i>

26:50.843 --> 26:53.746
- Which one do you like?

26:53.880 --> 27:00.753
<i>* *</i>

27:09.962 --> 27:13.199
<i>- * You *</i>

27:13.332 --> 27:15.802
<i>* I'd be lost without you *</i>

27:15.935 --> 27:19.171
<i>* Ooh ooh *</i>

27:19.305 --> 27:22.675
<i>* Oh you *</i>

27:22.809 --> 27:25.511
<i>* I'd be lost without you *</i>

27:25.644 --> 27:27.613
<i>* Ooh ooh *</i>

27:32.151 --> 27:34.220
- Mmm, mmm, mmm.

27:35.755 --> 27:38.324
Mmm, mmm, mmm.

27:45.164 --> 27:47.633
- Got enough for me?

27:53.139 --> 27:54.673
- Take it.

27:54.807 --> 27:56.709
But if it's money you want,
I'm not giving you any.

27:56.843 --> 27:59.445
- Hey.
Who paid to fix those teeth?

27:59.578 --> 28:01.047
-
- Me.

28:01.180 --> 28:02.414
Who got you off the sweets,

28:02.548 --> 28:05.184
taught you what a salad
is, huh?

28:05.317 --> 28:06.986
Yeah,
I whipped you into shape.

28:07.119 --> 28:11.657
And now the bill is coming due,
Christine Collins,

28:11.791 --> 28:15.094
with your big life
and your fancy friends.

28:15.227 --> 28:16.863
- You don't know anything
about my life.

28:16.996 --> 28:19.165
- I know you're ashamed
of who you really are.

28:19.298 --> 28:22.034
Trailer park hick
with a trailer park hick mom.

28:22.168 --> 28:23.535
- Don't you talk about her!

28:23.669 --> 28:25.738
- You're gonna take care
of me, Crystal Joe.

28:25.872 --> 28:27.706
- No!
- Or I'll make sure

28:27.840 --> 28:29.575
everybody knows you're nothing.
- Shut up.

28:29.708 --> 28:31.410
- Then again, maybe your life's
as empty as you are.

28:31.543 --> 28:34.113
Just a pretty little
made-for-TV package,

28:34.246 --> 28:37.750
but unwrap it,
and nothing there.

28:37.884 --> 28:41.353
- I am a successful, powerful,
happy woman!

28:41.487 --> 28:44.490
- No! You just play one on TV.

28:47.593 --> 28:48.795
- Aah!

28:53.532 --> 28:55.401
- Stop pretending.

28:55.534 --> 28:58.704
After 50 years, I know how you
breathe when you're asleep.

29:00.973 --> 29:03.075
Well, now we know why
we didn't do drugs

29:03.209 --> 29:06.145
last time we were this age.

29:06.278 --> 29:09.849
Mmm. What was I thinking?

29:09.982 --> 29:12.084
- Mmm.

29:18.190 --> 29:20.392
Hey, come here, baby.
Come here for sec.

29:20.526 --> 29:22.328
Come closer. Come on now.

29:22.461 --> 29:23.796
- I'm comin'.

29:27.499 --> 29:29.969
- When we met,

29:30.102 --> 29:33.405
you had a--a friend, a...

29:33.539 --> 29:36.508
a close friend.

29:38.744 --> 29:41.580
- Meredith?
- Yeah.

29:41.713 --> 29:44.250
Yeah, and then one day,
seemed like she just...

29:44.383 --> 29:46.385
disappeared.

29:48.120 --> 29:51.523
- Yeah, well, we, uh,
we grew apart, so--

29:51.657 --> 29:55.161
-
Stop pretending.

29:55.294 --> 29:56.662
After 50 years, I know when

29:56.795 --> 29:59.065
you're not telling me
the truth.

30:02.101 --> 30:03.569
You loved her.
- Mel.

30:03.702 --> 30:04.937
- Ruby...

30:06.738 --> 30:08.274
All this time, and I feel like

30:08.407 --> 30:10.476
I'm just understanding
who you are and...

30:13.112 --> 30:15.114
I feel like a fool.

30:15.247 --> 30:19.085
- You are not a fool.

30:19.218 --> 30:22.554
50 years ago, I made a choice.

30:22.688 --> 30:27.359
I chose you and the life
that we would build together.

30:27.493 --> 30:29.328
I wouldn't trade that
for the world.

30:29.461 --> 30:31.030
- Yeah, but you don't--

30:34.300 --> 30:37.904
You don't love me
the way that I love you.

30:38.037 --> 30:41.240
- But I do love you, Mel.

30:43.442 --> 30:44.443
You--

30:47.079 --> 30:49.481
You're the finest person
I've ever known.

30:51.783 --> 30:56.522
And you filled my life
with so much joy.

30:56.655 --> 31:02.828
And I will keep loving you
until my last breath.

31:02.962 --> 31:05.131
Do you hear me?

31:41.267 --> 31:44.370
- You made it just in time
for your parting feast.

31:44.503 --> 31:46.905
- I did something awful.
- I think we finally know

31:47.039 --> 31:49.408
what will satisfy your hunger.

31:51.310 --> 31:53.812
This should hit the spot.

31:56.882 --> 32:02.521
<i>* *</i>

32:02.654 --> 32:05.124
- Landon?

32:17.903 --> 32:21.273
<i>* *</i>

32:21.407 --> 32:23.142
- It's kind of early
for a swim.

32:32.751 --> 32:36.888
- I keep telling myself
to swim out and keep going.

32:37.023 --> 32:42.094
But, you know,
I--I can't make myself do it.

32:42.228 --> 32:44.863
Truth is I...

32:44.997 --> 32:47.633
I was never planning
on coming back from this trip.

32:47.766 --> 32:51.170
I said my goodbyes, 'cause
after this, it's just pain.

32:51.303 --> 32:56.442
And more pain and, uh...

32:56.575 --> 32:58.477
Hmm.

32:58.610 --> 33:00.679
Do you have a family?

33:00.812 --> 33:02.648
- I have a big family.
- Oh.

33:02.781 --> 33:06.252
- Yes.
But I--I haven't seen them

33:06.385 --> 33:08.287
in a really long time.

33:09.888 --> 33:12.191
- Well, I bet this job
doesn't stop

33:12.324 --> 33:14.193
for birthdays
or holidays, does it?

33:14.326 --> 33:18.064
- Not exactly.
- And I bet that's hard.

33:18.197 --> 33:20.332
- It can be.

33:20.466 --> 33:22.868
The Island chose me
for this role.

33:23.001 --> 33:26.705
- You didn't want it?
- I tried to say no.

33:26.838 --> 33:31.743
I was young. I was in love.
I...

33:31.877 --> 33:33.379
I'm sorry, 'cause I don't
usually

33:33.512 --> 33:35.447
talk about myself at all.

33:35.581 --> 33:37.149
- Must be the company.

33:37.283 --> 33:40.219
- No, no, actually,
I don't think so.

33:42.554 --> 33:47.226
No complaints. I have
the best job in the world.

33:47.359 --> 33:48.994
And I live in paradise.

33:49.128 --> 33:51.963
- Oh, you sure do.

33:52.098 --> 33:55.401
I'd love to stay
a little longer, in fact.

33:55.534 --> 34:00.172
But I--I got some dying to do.

34:00.306 --> 34:02.074
- Ruby--
- No, no, no, no.

34:02.208 --> 34:08.580
It's all right, really.
You know, I've had a good run.

34:09.748 --> 34:13.685
You know, if I were brave,
I'd spare Mel what's coming.

34:13.819 --> 34:18.757
You know, I just--
I've never been brave.

34:18.890 --> 34:23.695
Strong, yes. But not brave.

34:30.402 --> 34:32.471
- Well, there are many ways
to be brave

34:32.604 --> 34:35.141
and many opportunities
for bravery.

34:37.409 --> 34:41.079
That just...
isn't the right one for you.

34:46.485 --> 34:48.520
Come on.

34:48.654 --> 34:50.122
I'll walk you back, all right?

34:50.256 --> 34:52.090
- All right.

35:00.199 --> 35:01.467
- Mmm.

35:03.935 --> 35:08.240
Mmm. Mmm!

35:16.948 --> 35:18.717
Hello?
<i>- Good morning.</i>

35:18.850 --> 35:20.986
<i>Would you like breakfast
in your room this morning?</i>

35:21.119 --> 35:24.656
- Breakfast. No, thank you.
I'm--

35:27.058 --> 35:29.127
I'm not hungry.

35:36.668 --> 35:38.704
- Oh, great. You're here.

35:38.837 --> 35:40.272
Thank you so much
for meeting me.

35:40.406 --> 35:42.174
- Oh, okay.
- You know, the work that I do

35:42.308 --> 35:44.976
as a steward of this island
is--is an honor.

35:45.110 --> 35:46.712
I help people.

35:46.845 --> 35:49.981
I transform their lives
always for the better.

35:50.115 --> 35:52.251
You know, in the past,
people in my position,

35:52.384 --> 35:57.189
they have had a second,
a right hand.

35:57.323 --> 36:01.793
Ruby, I would like to
invite you

36:01.927 --> 36:05.030
to stay on Fantasy Island.

36:08.467 --> 36:10.035
- You--you'd like to what?

36:10.168 --> 36:12.904
- And you will remain
just as you are, healthy,

36:13.038 --> 36:16.308
strong, young, beautiful.

36:16.442 --> 36:19.711
Your tattoo.
What made you choose it?

36:19.845 --> 36:23.148
- I--I don't know.
I was drawn to it.

36:23.282 --> 36:26.852
- You know, it's an island
symbol of rebirth.

36:26.985 --> 36:29.888
It's reserved only to those
who hold the position

36:30.021 --> 36:31.723
that I'm offering you.

36:31.857 --> 36:35.227
I truly believe the Island
was speaking to you and to me.

36:36.862 --> 36:38.530
Well, why would the Island
speak to me?

36:38.664 --> 36:42.868
- You know, this island
is endlessly mysterious.

36:43.001 --> 36:45.203
But also, it's usually right.

36:48.374 --> 36:52.978
- Well, what do you think?
Could we?

36:53.111 --> 36:58.850
- I, uh... I think
it's a one-person offer, honey.

37:09.895 --> 37:12.798
- Well, then no.
- Ruby, on Fantasy Island,

37:12.931 --> 37:15.734
you know, honor
is balanced by--by sacrifice.

37:15.867 --> 37:19.037
- No, no. Absolutely not.

37:19.170 --> 37:23.241
How could you even ask me this?
What is wrong with you?

37:23.375 --> 37:26.512
- Yes. Yes, she'll stay.

37:26.645 --> 37:29.615
- No, you do not speak for me,
Mel Akuda.

37:29.748 --> 37:31.049
- Now don't be crazy.

37:31.182 --> 37:32.918
- No, I'm not gonna
talk about this.

37:33.051 --> 37:35.253
- Hey, we can tell the kids
that--that you didn't make it,

37:35.387 --> 37:36.588
that the trip was too much.

37:36.722 --> 37:41.427
- No! What?!
- Ruby, look at me.

37:41.560 --> 37:44.396
We both know that
you're gonna leave me soon.

37:44.530 --> 37:47.666
- Not like this I'm--
- Hey, hey, hey.

37:47.799 --> 37:53.038
You lived your whole life
for me, for our family.

37:53.171 --> 37:56.575
It's your turn now.

37:56.708 --> 37:59.277
Now, Ms. Roarke, she's--she's
offering you the opportunity

37:59.411 --> 38:04.383
at a whole new life
for yourself.

38:04.516 --> 38:07.285
And you can be yourself,
your whole self.

38:07.419 --> 38:10.622
I couldn't live with myself
if I let you pass that up.

38:13.124 --> 38:14.092
- Ruby...

38:16.662 --> 38:20.198
I'm offering you
an opportunity to be brave.

38:24.069 --> 38:30.976
<i>* *</i>

38:42.120 --> 38:44.122
- Good morning.
-

38:44.255 --> 38:49.695
I had the strangest
weekend of my life.

38:49.828 --> 38:53.064
Thank you.
- You're so welcome.

38:53.198 --> 38:57.803
- I feel liberated
and a little confused.

38:57.936 --> 38:59.204
Last night--

38:59.337 --> 39:03.875
- At the pig roast?
- The pig roast.

39:06.311 --> 39:11.850
I woke up and I thought--um,
it's hard to explain.

39:11.983 --> 39:14.019
- Christine, I want to tell
you,

39:14.152 --> 39:16.855
after you came to my office,
I looked into your stepfather.

39:16.988 --> 39:20.358
His death certificate says
that Landon Green died in 2012.

